State of the art, current Intel GPU bring-up frontier
======================================================

This file is a raw proof transcript.  Read it like the HDA log: every line
claims one hardware boundary and does not claim the next boundary.

Current proven claims in this capture:

- `pci-claim`: TrueOS claimed Intel GPU `00:02.0`, device `0x4680`,
  revision `0x0C`, with `0x1000000` bytes of MMIO.
- `guc-proof`: GuC firmware was found and bootstrap reached
  `bootrom=JUMP_PASSED`, `ukernel=READY`, `auth=0x2`.
- `display-proof`: primary boot surface is on `pipe-a`, live surface register
  matches `0x02000000`, and the logo path reports `ok=1`.
- `vf-proof`: `vf-streamout-proof`, `vf-draw-path`,
  `vs-draw-frontier`, and `vs-streamout-proof` report
  `vf-proof accepted=1` with IA counters moving.
- `clip-raster-proof`: `vf-draw-path` reports
  `clip-raster-proof accepted=1` with `cl_delta=1`, `cl_prim_delta=1`.
- `vs-proof`: `vs-draw-frontier` and `vs-streamout-proof` report
  `vs-proof accepted=1` with `vs_delta=3`, and shader upload matches the baked
  blob.

